Package slogo.compiler

Interface Workspace

public interface Workspace
Keeps track of all objects that extend WorkspaceEntry. Will notify the WorkspaceViewController of any changes. Internally keeps the WorkspaceEntry objects in Collections. Command objects have direct access to this class because they frequently create or use objects in the workspace. For example, a NewFunctionCommand, once performer, would place all the function's required parameters as variables in the workspace, as well as the Function object it creates. When Function is running through its Token objects, if it comes across a generic Token type with no specific subclass, it will search through the workspace for a Variable or Function with a matching name.

  • Method Details

    • add

      boolean add​(WorkspaceEntry entry)
      Adds the passed WorkspaceEntry to the workspace. This also notifies the WorkspaceViewController of the addition. In the case that a WorkspaceEntry with the same name already exists, this operation will replace it with the most recently passed object.
      Parameters:
      entry - The WorkspaceEntry to add to the workspace.
      Returns:
      Returns true if the addition is successful, otherwise return false.

    • search

      WorkspaceEntry search​(java.lang.String name)
      Returns the WorkspaceEntry with the matching name identifier. If not found, return null.
      Parameters:
      name - search String.
      Returns:
      the WorkspaceEntry matching the search name, or null.
